data.description:
Conveniently located on the Southside of Jacksonville with new construction nearby, this lovingly updated home offers the perfect blend of space and comfort.  Recent renovations from kitchen appliances and flooring (7/2022) to a new roof (8/2019) and triple-paned windows (10/2022) have breathed new life into this vintage gem. Three bedrooms provide ample space for relaxation and the primary bedroom features a convenient half bath for added privacy. The enclosed carport even has the necessary plumbing for a 2nd full bathroom. This home has also been thoughtfully updated with a modern HVAC (5/2022), new plumbing drains and piping (8/2021), and electrical systems (8/2021). What a savings and added peace of mind for the next owner!  See the supplemental tab for all updates. The enclosed carport area has plumbing for a 2nd shower and a drain pipe for the sink and toilet. The new owner can easily add the shower pan and drywall, tile, and enclose the area to their liking.  An opening to the bedroom and half-bath area can also be added to connect the spaces or have a 2.5-bath home.

The home appraised above the original list price before the July 2023 updates.

New Roof: 8/2019
Gutters installed: 7/2023
New AC: 5/2022
Triple-paned glass windows with Lifetime transferrable warranty: 10/2022
New Plumbing drains and water lines in kitchen and bathrooms: 8/2021
New Whirlpool stainless steel kitchen appliances: oven, refrigerator, microwave, dishwasher 7/2022
Kitchen counters and soft-close doors and drawers updated: 8/2021
New ceiling fans and electrical updates: 8/2021
Carbon monoxide/smoke detectors: 7/2023
Home exterior painted: 7/2023
New carpet: 6/2022
Pest control & termite treatment: 8/2022
Rheem hot water heater: 2018
